prototypes.description:
Work resulting from the flow of electrons from a negative to a positive source. Example: A power belt sander imports a flow of electricity from a wall outlet and transforms it into a rotation.
i. Electromotive force. Potential difference across the positive and negative sources. Example: Household electrical receptacles provide a flow of electromotive force of 110 V.
ii. Current. The flow or rate of flow of electric charge in a conductor or medium between two points having a difference in potential. Example: Circuit breakers trip when the current exceeds a specified limit.
